Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3⁄4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Ponzu Sauce{12%ml}, half the @Umami Ginger Sauce{4%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings), half the @Rice Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon} (all for 4), and @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste.

> TIP: If you like a sweeter sauce, stir in a pinch of sugar.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring, until just softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Ground Beef{10%ounce} and @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}; season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Using a #spatula{}, press beef into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break up meat into pieces and continue to cook, stirring, until beef is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in ponzu-ginger mixture and cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, ~{1%minute} more.

> Rinse shrimp under cold water, then pat dry with paper towels. Swap in shrimp or beef for pork (no need to break up shrimp into pieces!).

Stir in @Coleslaw Mix{4%ounce} and scallion greens to same pan; cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with stir-fry and @Crispy Fried Onions{1}. Pick @Cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly tear and sprinkle over bowls. Drizzle with any remaining Sriracha if desired and serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.